.TH "of_dma_router_register" 9 "of_dma_router_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_dma_router_register \- Register a DMA router to DT DMA helpers as a controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_dma_router_register
.BI "(struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "void *(*of_dma_route_allocate) (struct of_phandle_args *, struct of_dma *) "  ","
.BI "struct dma_router *dma_router "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
device node of DMA router
.IP "of_dma_route_allocate" 12
setup function for the router which need to
modify the dma_spec for the DMA controller to
use and to set up the requested route.
.IP "dma_router" 12
pointer to dma_router structure to be used when
the route need to be free up.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success or appropriate errno value on error.

Allocated memory should be freed with appropriate \fBof_dma_controller_free\fP
call.
